Nerve's source code is an independent, from-scratch implementation. It contains
no third-party source and requires no third-party library at runtime.

Model weights are not part of this source distribution. The conversion tools
under studies/ (convert.c, convert_hf.py, convert_minilm.py) are one-time
import utilities: the weights they read are supplied by the user and remain
governed by their own licences, which are independent of this one.
